-- Mexico’s Bank Lending Rose 9.7 Percent in November
-- B y   J o s e   E n r i q u e   A r r i o j a
-- 2011-12-30T15:54:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-30/mexico-s-bank-lending-rose-9-7-percent-in-november-correct-.html
(Corrects to fix amount of lending to trillion from
billion pesos in second paragraph.)  Mexico ’s bank lending, excluding
loans from development banks, rose 9.7 percent in inflation-
adjusted terms in November from a year earlier, the nation’s
central bank said today in a report published on its website.  Commercial banks lent a total of 3.08 trillion pesos,
Banxico, as the central bank is known, said in its  monthly
lending  report.  Loans to consumers increased 19.2 percent while mortgages
rose 4.1 percent, the report showed.  Bank lending, excluding from development banks, rose 12.3
percent in inflation-adjusted terms in October, the nation’s
central bank said in a  report  published Nov. 30.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jose Enrique Arrioja in Mexico City at 
